TITLE::CodexComposite
summary::Development platform for creating composite classes of scriptable objects.
categories::Libraries>CodexIan>CodexComposites
related::Guides/MusicalCompositing, Classes/Hybrid
keyword::composite, compositing, codexian, composition

DESCRIPTION::
teletype::CodexComposite:: establishes a workflow both for developing and interacting with composite objects, namely those which are comprised of interconnected scriptable modules. CodexComposite is responsible for maintaing a directory that each of its subclasses populates with their own modular collections. 

Moreover, teletype::CodexComposite:: defines an interface for easily manipulating these collections, allowing new modules to be generated from templates (see link::Classes/Templater::), cloned from existing collections, and also both loaded and reloaded without recompiling teletype::sclang::. In this way, each teletype::CodexComposite::-typed class is free to focus on defining interesting interactions between modules rather than dealing with the pesky details of their storage and organization.  

note::teletype::CodexComposite:: is a development tool that should not be instantiated. Rather, it is meant to encapsulate behaviors on behalf of its subclasses. So instance those instead.
::

